'''Aymeric Jean Louis Gérard Alphonse Laporte Fevre''' ({{IPA|fr|ɛ.mə.ʁik la.pɔʁt}}; born 27 May 1994) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Athletic Bilbao]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]].

When he joined Athletic Bilbao in 2010 at the age of 16, he became only the second player born in France—after [[Bixente Lizarazu]]—to play for them, going on to make 222 competitive appearances for the club. In January 2018, he signed for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]. He was part of the side which won the only [[Treble (association football)#Domestic trebles|domestic treble]] in English men's football in [[2018–19 Manchester City F.C. season|2019]], and the country's second-ever [[Treble (association football)#Continental trebles|continental treble]] in [[2022–23 Manchester City F.C. season|2023]]. He moved to Saudi club [[Al Nassr FC|Al-Nassr]] in 2023 and spent two seasons there before returning to Athletic Bilbao in September 2025.

Laporte won 51 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] for France at [[France national youth football team|youth international levels]], and was called up to the [[France national football team|senior team]] twice but remained uncapped. In 2021, after receiving [[Spanish citizenship]], Laporte was named in Spain's squad for [[UEFA Euro 2020]]. He would then go on to represent the nation at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]], winning the latter tournament.

==Early life==
Aymeric Jean Louis Gérard Alphonse Laporte<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/-/media/files/thefaportal/governance-docs/registrations/january-2018.ashx |title=List of Players under Written Contract Registered Between 01/01/2018 and 31/01/2018 |publisher=The Football Association |page=5|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024155231/http://www.thefa.com/-/media/files/thefaportal/governance-docs/registrations/january-2018.ashx|archive-date=24 October 2019}}</ref> was born on 27 May 1994<ref>{{Cite web |title=Aymeric Laporte |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/aymeric-laporte-254251/ |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=11v11.com}}</ref> in [[Agen]], Lot-et-Garonne, France, and is of [[Basques|Basque]] descent through his great-grandparents.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Beltrán |first=Javi |date=2013-07-25 |title=Laporte: "Tengo sangre vasca por parte de mis bisabuelos" |trans-title=Laporte: "I have Basque blood through my great-grandparents" |url=https://www.eldesmarque.com/futbol/athletic-club/20130725/laporte-tengo-sangre-vasca-por-parte-de-mis-bisabuelos_60036668.html |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=ElDesmarque |language=es}}</ref> He started playing football and [[Rugby football|rugby]] at the age of five, and began his development at [[SU Agen Football|Agen]]'s football academy.<ref name=Among>{{cite web |url=http://onlyfootball.fr/?p=513 |title=Aymeric Laporte, un Basque parmi les Basques|trans-title=Aymeric Laporte, a Basque among the Basques |website=Only Football |language=fr |date=14 May 2013 |access-date=12 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303203653/http://onlyfootball.fr/?p=513|archive-date=3 March 2016}}</ref><ref name=Bio>{{cite web |url=http://www.aymericlaporte.com/en/bio/ |title=Biography – Athletic Bilbao signing and beginnings |publisher=Aymeric Laporte official website |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171028201223/http://www.aymericlaporte.com/en/bio/ |archive-date=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Karouri |first=Khaled |date=2012-11-04 |title=Entretien avec… Aymeric Laporte : " S'entraîner avec Fernando Llorente, ce n'est pas donné à tout le monde " |url=https://www.footmercato.net/a200801204779500042-entretien-avec-aymeric-laporte-sentrainer-avec-fernando-llorente-ce-nest-pas-donne-a-tout-le-monde |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=Foot Mercato : Info Transferts Football - Actu Foot Transfert |language=fr}}</ref> In 2009, he was invited to join [[Athletic Bilbao]] after being scouted.<ref name=Among/><ref name=Bio/> By arrangement with the club, he spent a season with [[Aviron Bayonnais FC|Bayonne]]<ref name=Bio/><ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Delorme |first=Robin |date=2013-09-26 |title=Aymeric Laporte a " arrêté de regarder les papillons " |url=https://www.sofoot.com/articles/aymeric-laporte-a-arrete-de-regarder-les-papillons-espagne-liga-6e-journee-athletic-bilbao-betis-seville |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=SOFOOT.com |language=fr}}</ref> as he was too young to move outside France at the time.{{citation needed|date=May 2022}}

==Club career==
===Athletic Bilbao===
[[File:Aymeric Laporte(cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Laporte playing for [[Athletic Bilbao]] in 2014]]
Laporte arrived in [[Bilbao]] formally in 2010,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Clayton |first=David |title=Laporte's Journey |url=https://www.mancity.com/features/laporte-journey/ |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=www.mancity.com |language=en}}</ref> joining Athletic's youth setup at [[Lezama Facilities|Lezama]], prompting debate locally over whether his signing met the criteria of [[Athletic Bilbao signing policy|their policy]] due to his tenuous links to the [[Basque Country (greater region)|Basque region]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Beltrán |first=Javi |date=2013-07-25 |title=Laporte: "Tengo sangre vasca por parte de mis bisabuelos" |url=https://www.eldesmarque.com/futbol/athletic-club/20130725/laporte-tengo-sangre-vasca-por-parte-de-mis-bisabuelos_60036668.html |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=ElDesmarque |language=es}}</ref><ref name=":0" /> He went on to play for the club's [[CD Basconia|farm]] and [[Athletic Bilbao B|reserve teams]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/deportes/20120428/54286365543/aymeric-laporte-cachorro-valioso.html |title=Aymeric Laporte, el cachorro más valioso|trans-title=Aymeric Laporte, most valuable pup |newspaper=La Vanguardia |first=Roberto |last=Rodríguez |location=Barcelona |language=es |date=28 April 2012 |access-date=15 May 2013}}</ref> On 28 November 2012 he was given his debut with the main squad by manager [[Marcelo Bielsa]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sport.sfr.fr/football/premier-league/de-bielsa-a-guardiola-laporte-raconte-ses-mentors.html |title=De Bielsa à Guardiola: Laporte raconte ses mentors|trans-title=From Bielsa to Guardiola: Laporte tells his mentors |publisher=SFR |language=fr |date=25 February 2018 |access-date=5 June 2018}}</ref> playing the full 90 minutes in a 2–0 away win against [[Hapoel Ironi Kiryat Shmona F.C.|Hapoel Ironi Kiryat Shmona]] in [[2012–13 UEFA Europa League|that season]]'s [[UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2010004--h-kiryat-shmona-vs-athletic-club/ |title=Athletic post comfortable Kiryat Shmona win |publisher=UEFA |date=28 November 2012 |access-date=5 December 2012}}</ref>

Laporte made his first [[La Liga]] appearance on 9 December 2012, playing one minute in a 1–0 home win over [[Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Delfín |first=Melero |title=Athletic-Celta: resumen, goles y resultado - MARCA.com |url=https://www.marca.com/eventos/marcador/futbol/2012_13/primera/jornada_15/ath_cel/ |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=www.marca.com}}</ref> He was named in the starting line-up the following week, helping Bilbao to defeat [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]] by the same scoreline,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://espnfc.com/uk/en/report/348361/report.html?soccernet=true&cc=5739 |title=Aduriz wins it for Bilbao |website=ESPN Soccernet |date=15 December 2012 |access-date=16 December 2012}}</ref> and was definitely promoted to the first team shortly after, signing a new contract until 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.athletic-club.eus/cas/noticias/12731/laporte-jugador-de-la-primera-plantilla.html |title=Laporte, jugador de la primera plantilla|trans-title=Laporte, first-team player |publisher=Athletic Bilbao |language=es |date=17 December 2012 |access-date=21 January 2015}}</ref> On 14 January 2013, he was given the number four shirt previously worn by [[Ustaritz Aldekoaotalora|Ustaritz]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.athletic-club.eus/cas/noticias/12779/dorsal-de-aymeric-laporte.html |title=Dorsal de Aymeric Laporte|trans-title=Aymeric Laporte's number |publisher=Athletic Bilbao |language=es |date=14 January 2013 |access-date=21 January 2015}}</ref> and late in the month he renewed his contract, running until 2016 and with a €27.5&nbsp;million release clause.<ref>{{cite news |last=Beato |first=Rafa |date=28 January 2013 |title=Laporte renueva hasta 2016 |trans-title=Laporte renews until 2016 |url=http://www.marca.com/2013/01/28/futbol/equipos/athletic/1359380216.html |access-date=2025-04-06 |newspaper=Marca |location=Madrid |language=es}}</ref>

Laporte became a regular starter under new coach [[Ernesto Valverde]], also being deployed at [[left-back]] on occasion.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ligabbva.es/3228_athletic-de-bilbao/2160744_valverde-prueba-a-laporte-de-lateral-y-saborit-de-interior.html |title=Valverde prueba a Laporte de lateral y Saborit de interior|trans-title=Valverde tries Laporte as fullback and Saborit as winger |publisher=Liga BBVA |language=es |date=6 August 2013 |access-date=22 October 2016|archive-url=https://archive.today/20131212163520/http://www.ligabbva.es/3228_athletic-de-bilbao/2160744_valverde-prueba-a-laporte-de-lateral-y-saborit-de-interior.html|archive-date=12 December 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Uriarte |first=M. |date=3 October 2013 |title=Charla de Valverde con Laporte |trans-title=Valverde lectures Laporte |url=http://www.marca.com/2013/10/03/futbol/equipos/athletic/1380786727.html |access-date=2025-04-06 |newspaper=Marca |location=Madrid |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=García |first=Alberto |date=7 December 2013 |title=Un descanso para Laporte y entran Aduriz, Morán y Etxeita |trans-title=Rest for Laporte, in with Aduriz, Morán and Etxeita |url=http://www.mundodeportivo.com/20131207/athletic-bilbao/un-descanso-para-laporte-y-entran-aduriz-moran-y-etxeita_54395264363.html |access-date=2025-04-06 |newspaper=Mundo Deportivo |location=Barcelona |language=es}}</ref> He scored his first goal as a professional on 28 October 2013, netting the game's only goal at [[Getafe CF|Getafe]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://espnfc.com/en/report/373118/report.html?soccernet=true&cc=null |title=Laporte earns win for Bilbao |website=ESPN FC |date=28 October 2013 |access-date=22 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131207132838/http://espnfc.com/en/report/373118/report.html?soccernet=true&cc=null|archive-date=7 December 2013}}</ref> At the end of [[2013–14 La Liga|2013–14 league season]], he was voted into the [[LFP Awards#Team of the Year|La Liga Team of the Year]] by the reporters of the [[Liga de Fútbol Profesional]].<ref name=2014a>{{cite web |url=http://www.laliga.es/en/news/the-liga-bbva-team-of-the-season |title=The Liga BBVA team of the season |publisher=La Liga |date=19 May 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181205133841/https://www.laliga.es/en/news/the-liga-bbva-team-of-the-season |archive-date=5 December 2018}}</ref><ref name=2014b>{{cite web |url=http://www.insidespanishfootball.com/108784/lfp-reporters-choose-their-la-liga-ideal-eleven-for-2013-14/ |title=LFP reporters choose their La Liga 'Ideal Eleven' for 2013–14 |website=Inside Spanish Football |first=Heath |last=Chesters |date=19 May 2014 |access-date=24 January 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160130072042/http://www.insidespanishfootball.com/108784/lfp-reporters-choose-their-la-liga-ideal-eleven-for-2013-14/ |archive-date=30 January 2016}}</ref>

In June 2015, Laporte extended his link until 2019 with a release clause of €50&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/athletic-bilbao/story/2480397/aymeric-laporte-signs-four-year-athletic-bilbao-deal |title=Aymeric Laporte signs four-year deal to remain at Athletic Bilbao |website=ESPN FC |date=5 June 2015 |access-date=28 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=sport |first=Guardian |date=2015-06-05 |title=Athletic Bilbao's Aymeric Laporte signs new contract with €50m release clause |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/jun/05/aymeric-laporte-athletic-bilbao-new-contract |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> After losing the [[2015 Copa del Rey Final]] to [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]],<ref>{{Cite news |last=Lowe |first=Sid |date=2015-05-30 |title=Lionel Messi double gives Barcelona Cup final win over Athletic Bilbao |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/may/30/athletic-bilbao-barcelona-copa-del-rey-final-match-report |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=The Observer |language=en-GB |issn=0029-7712}}</ref> he played both legs of the [[2015 Supercopa de España]] triumph against the same opposition, Athletic's first silverware for 31 years.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Athletic 4-0 Barcelona (14 Aug, 2015) Game Analysis - ESPN (UK) |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/427686 |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

On 13 June 2016, Laporte renewed his contract until 2020, with his buyout clause rising to an initial €65&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2016-06-13 |title=Laporte signs new Athletic Bilbao contract |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37474924/aymeric-laporte-signs-new-athletic-bilbao-contract |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2018-01-29 |title=Athletic Club: Manchester City pay Laporte's 65m euros buyout clause |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/2018/01/29/5a6f3c9122601d6a018b4612.html |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=MARCA in English |language=en}}</ref>

===Manchester City===
Near the end of the winter transfer window of January 2018, Laporte signed for [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] for a reported fee of £57&nbsp;million<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-01-30 |title=Aymeric Laporte: Manchester City sign French defender for club record £57m |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/42873612 |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> (his contractual [[release clause]] amount and a record-breaking figure for both clubs). He was given the number 14 shirt,<ref>{{Cite news |last=sport |first=Guardian |date=2018-01-30 |title=Manchester City break transfer record to sign Aymeric Laporte for £57.2m |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jan/30/manchester-city-break-transfer-record-sign-aymeric-laporte-athletic-bilbao |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> while Athletic immediately spent around half of the fee on [[Iñigo Martínez]] as a replacement.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/athletic-bilbao-sign-martinez-from-real-sociedad/g2qcqw6nfa8t1fj74qrh862fb |title=Athletic Bilbao sign Inigo Martinez to replace Aymeric Laporte |website=Goal.com |publisher=DAZN Group |location=Leeds |first=Nicholas |last=McGee |date=30 January 2018 |access-date=30 January 2018}}</ref> Just one day after signing, Laporte made his Manchester City and [[Premier League]] debut against [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]]. City came out victorious winning 3–0 as they kept up their title charge.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Clayton |first=David |title=Blues extend lead at top with comfortable win |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/first-team/match-report/2018/january/man-city-v-west-brom-match-report |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=www.mancity.com |language=en}}</ref> He went on to make 13 appearances throughout the season for City, helping them accumulate an unprecedented 100 points in a Premier League season. He made a total of nine league appearances meaning he was eligible for a winner's medal.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Aymeric Laporte Al-Nassr Defender, Profile & Stats {{!}} Premier League |url=https://www.premierleague.com/players/11044/Aymeric-Laporte/overview |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=www.premierleague.com |language=en}}</ref>

Laporte scored his first goal for City on 25 August 2018, equalising against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in a 1–1 away draw.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2018-08-23 |title=Wolves 1-1 Man City: Aymeric Laporte rescues Molineux draw for champions |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/45230636 |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He made 51 appearances during the 2018–19 season as the club completed the first domestic [[Treble (association football)|treble]] in English football history ([[2018–19 Premier League|Premier League]], [[2018–19 FA Cup|FA Cup]], [[2018–19 EFL Cup|League Cup]], plus the [[2018 FA Community Shield|Community Shield]]).<ref>{{Cite news |last=McNulty |first=Phil |date=2019-05-17 |title=Man City 6-0 Watford: City clinch historic domestic treble |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48236232 |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> He scored five goals throughout the season, including an important goal on the final day of the Premier League campaign as City romped to victory over [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] securing back-to-back league titles and the second of Laporte's career. Overall he played a total of 4,352 minutes.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Aymeric Laporte {{!}} Football Stats {{!}} Al-Nassr {{!}} Season 2018/2019 {{!}} Soccer Base |url=https://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=68462&season_id=151 |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=www.soccerbase.com}}</ref> On 31 August 2019, Laporte sustained an injury to his right knee, causing him to be carried off on a stretcher.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |date=2019-08-31 |title=City fear Laporte out 'for a while' with knee injury |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/37576085/city-fear-laporte-while-knee-injury |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Aarons |first=Ed |date=2025-04-02 |title=hello88 |url=https://thetimeinmusic.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131009053945/http://www.thetimeinmusic.com/ |url-status=usurped |archive-date=9 October 2013 |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=thetimeinmusic.com |language=en-GB}}</ref> He underwent surgery in September 2019.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2019-09-04 |title=Aymeric Laporte: Manchester City defender has surgery on right knee |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/49576729 |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

Laporte had been a regular starter for Manchester City after his return from injury during the 2019–20 season and through the start of the 2020–21 season until a poor display in a 2–0 defeat to [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] on 21 November 2020.<ref name=":2">{{Cite news |last=Jackson |first=Jamie |date=2021-01-19 |title=Pep Guardiola says Aymeric Laporte can decide own future at Manchester City |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/jan/19/pep-guardiola-aymeric-laporte-decide-own-future-manchester-city |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> [[John Stones]] replaced Laporte in the centre of defence and formed a formidable partnership with new signing [[Rúben Dias]] in Laporte's absence from the starting line-up.<ref name=":2" /> On 25 April 2021, Laporte headed in the only goal of the game as City beat Tottenham to win their fourth straight [[2021 EFL Cup Final|EFL Cup]].<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Burt |first1=Jason |last2=Bagchi |first2=Rob |last3=Edwards |first3=Luke |date=2021-04-25 |title=Aymeric Laporte makes it four Carabao Cups in a row for dominant Man City against outclassed Spurs |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2021/04/25/manchester-city-vs-tottenham-league-cup-final-2021-live-score/ |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=The Telegraph |language=en-GB |issn=0307-1235}}</ref>

===Al-Nassr===
On 24 August 2023, Laporte left Manchester City and joined [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al Nassr FC|Al-Nassr]] for a fee of £23.6&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-08-24 |title=Aymeric Laporte leaves Manchester City for Al Nassr in £23.6m move |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66602657 |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Bosher |first=Luke |date=2023-08-24 |title=Aymeric Laporte completes move to Al Nassr from Manchester City |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4799449/2023/08/24/aymeric-laporte-al-nassr-saudi-transfer/#:~:text=Aymeric%20Laporte%20has%20completed%20his,0%20victory%20over%20Newcastle%20United. |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> He made 69 appearances for the [[Riyadh]]-based club over two seasons, including the [[2024 Saudi Super Cup final]], but missed the [[2024 King Cup final]].

===Return to Athletic Bilbao===
In the summer of 2025, Laporte's former club Athletic Bilbao (short of defenders with the [[Doping in sport|doping]] suspension of [[Yeray Alvarez]] and a long-term injury to understudy [[Unai Egiluz]]) were reported as having agreed personal terms for a return to Spain, with Al-Nassr signing [[Iñigo Martínez]] as a replacement in an echo of the events of 2018<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/athletic-bilbao/20250808/1002511696/laporte-inigo-martinez-vueltas-da-futbol.html|title=Laporte, Iñigo Martínez y las vueltas que da el fútbol|language=es|trans-title=Laporte, Iñigo Martínez and the twists and turns of football|work=Mundo Deportivo|first=Endika|last=Río|date=8 August 2025|access-date=11 September 2025}}</ref> – Martínez was included in the squad for the [[2025 Saudi Super Cup]] while Laporte did not travel to [[Hong Kong]] for the tournament. However, complications over the nature of the transaction (Laporte was said to be negotiating a release from the final year of his contract which was not well received by the Al-Nassr hierarchy)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/aymeric-laporte-denied-dream-athletic-club-return-as-fifa-reject-transfer-after-al-nassr-fail-to-submit-paperwork-on-time/blt433cd9176eb4fa5f|title=Aymeric Laporte denied dream Athletic Club return as FIFA reject transfer after Al-Nassr fail to submit paperwork on time|work=Goal.com|first=Nukul|last=Jashoria|date=3 September 2025|access-date=11 September 2025}}</ref> caused the process to be delayed from the Saudi end; no deal was concluded prior to the closure of the Spanish [[transfer window]] on 1 September and FIFA initially declined to grant an exceptional [[FIFA Transfer Matching System|International Transfer Certificate]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/2025/09/03/official-statement-about-aymeric-laporte/ |title=Official Statement about Aymeric Laporte|work=Athletic Club|date=3 September 2025|access-date=11 September 2025}}</ref> On 11 September, it was confirmed that the ITC had been granted on appeal and Laporte rejoined Athletic on a three-year contract<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/2025/09/11/aymeric-laporte-rejoins-athletic-club/|title=Aymeric Laporte rejoins Athletic Club|work=Athletic Club|date=11 September 2025|access-date=11 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cn76g3ggdydo|title=Laporte joins Athletic Bilbao after Fifa approval|work=BBC Sport|date=11 September 2025|access-date=11 September 2025}}</ref> for a reported €10 million fee.<ref>[https://tribuna.com/en/news/2025-09-12-aymeric-laportes-transfer-to-athletic-club-was-delayed-due-to-alnassr-having-better-offer/ Aymeric Laporte's transfer to Athletic Club was delayed due to Al-Nassr having better offers from other clubs - reports], Tribuna.com, 12 September 2025</ref>

==International career==
===France===
Laporte represented [[France national football team|France]] at [[France national under-17 football team|under-17]], [[France national under-18 football team|under-18]], [[France national under-19 football team|under-19]] and [[France national under-21 football team|under-21 levels]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.mundodeportivo.com/20140227/futbol/laporte-convocado-para-la-sub-21-por-francia_54402647025.html |title=Laporte, convocado para la sub 21 por Francia|trans-title=Laporte, called up to France under-21 |newspaper=Mundo Deportivo |location=Barcelona |language=es |date=27 February 2014 |access-date=22 April 2014}}</ref> [[Captain (association football)|captaining]] each side.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2015-10-07 |title=Bilbao's Laporte would consider Spain call |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/37437463/athletic-bilbao-aymeric-laporte-consider-spain-call |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> He was part of the team that came runners-up to [[Serbia national under-19 football team|Serbia]] in the [[2013 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]] in Lithuania, and was selected in the Team of the Tournament.<ref name="UEFA">{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/under19/season=2013/technical-report/tr-under19-2013.pdf |title=Technical report |publisher=UEFA |pages=18–19 |access-date=11 April 2016}}{{dead link|date=March 2025|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>

On 24 March 2016, in a [[2017 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification Group 3|2017 European Under-21 Championship qualifier]] against [[Scotland national under-21 football team|Scotland]] in [[Angers]], Laporte was stretchered off with a fracture and dislocation to his right [[fibula]] and ankle, concluding his season prematurely.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Menezes |first=Jack de |date=2016-03-25 |title=Laporte's serious injury throws City's transfer plans in doubt |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/transfers/aymeric-laporte-injury-manchester-city-transfer-plans-dealt-a-blow-as-top-target-suffers-serious-injury-a6951786.html |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=The Independent |language=en}}</ref> Previously, in October 2015, he stated that he would consider representing [[Spain national football team|Spain]] if not selected by France for [[UEFA Euro 2016]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2015-10-07 |title=Bilbao's Laporte would consider Spain call |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37437463/athletic-bilbao-aymeric-laporte-consider-spain-call |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> In August 2016, at the behest of new national manager [[Julen Lopetegui]], Laporte began the process of making himself eligible for Spain.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/seleccion/2016/08/30/57c489e146163f72308b4591.html |title=Lopetegui 'ficha' a Laporte|trans-title=Lopetegui 'signs' Laporte |newspaper=Marca |location=Madrid |first=Enrique |last=Ortego |language=es |date=30 August 2016 |access-date=18 September 2016}}</ref> A month later, he was called up to the senior France squad by [[Didier Deschamps]] for [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group A|2018 World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] in October,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://sport24.lefigaro.fr/football/euro-2012/equipe-de-france/actualites/deschamps-appelle-laporte-et-laisse-giroud-a-la-maison-826710 |title=Équipe de France: Laporte arrive, Fekir revient|trans-title=France team: Laporte arrives, Fekir returns |newspaper=Le Figaro |location=Paris |language=fr |date=29 September 2016 |access-date=30 September 2016}}</ref> and stated he had decided not to apply for [[Spanish nationality law|Spanish nationality]] with the continued aim of playing for France.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://rmcsport.bfmtv.com/football/aymeric-laporte-je-pouvais-prendre-la-nationalite-espagnole-je-ne-l-ai-pas-fait-1043930.html |title=Aymeric Laporte: "Je pouvais prendre la nationalité espagnole, je ne l'ai pas fait"|trans-title=Aymeric Laporte: "I could take Spanish nationality, I did not do so" |publisher=BFM TV |language=fr |date=3 October 2016 |access-date=16 June 2017}}</ref> He did not take part in either match.{{citation needed|date=January 2024}}

In August 2019, he was called up for France's [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying Group H|UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]] fixtures against [[Albania national football team|Albania]] and [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/laporte-included-france-squad-euro-2020-qualifiers-130529339--sow.html |title=Laporte included in France squad for Euro 2020 qualifiers |website=Yahoo Sports |date=29 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191004050758/https://sports.yahoo.com/laporte-included-france-squad-euro-2020-qualifiers-130529339--sow.html |archive-date=4 October 2019}}</ref> However, two days later he was injured playing for his club and ruled out of any involvement.<ref name=":1" />

===Spain===
In May 2021, the [[Council of Ministers (Spain)|Spanish Council of Ministers]] granted Spanish nationality to Laporte following a process initiated on his behalf by the [[Royal Spanish Football Federation]] (RFEF). [[FIFA]] approved the change of association later that week, allowing him to play for Spain at the upcoming [[UEFA Euro 2020]] tournament.<ref>{{Cite web |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=2021-05-11 |title=Report: Laporte can play for Spain at Euro 2020 after nationality approved |url=https://www.thescore.com/euro_fed/news/2170835/report-laporte-to-play-for-spain-at-euro-2020-after-nationality-approved |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=theScore.com |language=en}}</ref> Laporte had previously claimed that "playing for Spain is out of the question" and that he would not apply for dual citizenship.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Jones |first=Matt |title=Aymeric Laporte Says Playing for Spain 'Out of the Question' Amid France Absence |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2811048-aymeric-laporte-says-playing-for-spain-out-of-the-question-amid-france-absence |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=bleacherreport.com |language=en}}</ref>

On 24 May 2021, Laporte was included in Spain's [[UEFA Euro 2020 squads#Spain|24-man squad]] for Euro 2020.<ref>{{Cite news |last=sport |first=Guardian |date=2021-05-24 |title=Spain leave Sergio Ramos out of Euro 2020 squad and call up Aymeric Laporte |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/may/24/spain-leave-sergio-ramos-out-of-euro-2020-squad-and-call-up-aymeric-laporte |access-date=2025-04-06 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 4 June, he made his Spain debut when he started in a friendly goalless draw with [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Aymeric Laporte Produces Sublime Piece Of Defending On Spain Debut |url=https://www.sportbible.com/football/news-aymeric-laporte-produces-sublime-piece-of-defending-on-spain-debut-20210604 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240125013301/https://www.sportbible.com/football/news-aymeric-laporte-produces-sublime-piece-of-defending-on-spain-debut-20210604 |archive-date=2024-01-25 |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=SPORTbible}}</ref> He scored his debut goal for the national team on 23 June, in the [[UEFA Euro 2020 Group E|group stage]] 5–0 routing of [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]].<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2021-06-23 |title='Terrible' Slovakia gift Spain biggest Euros win as Laporte justifies switch |url=https://talksport.com/football/900831/slovakia-spain-euro-2020-man-city-aymeric-laporte-france-ferran-torres/ |access-date=2025-04-06 |website=talkSPORT }}</ref>

On 14 July 2024, Laporte helped Spain win their fourth European title at [[UEFA Euro 2024]], playing in every knockout game as a starter.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-07-14 |title=Laporte and Nacho crowned Euro 2024 champions |url=https://www.spl.com.sa/en/news/503658/www.spl.com.sa/en/news/503658/laporte-and-nacho-crowned-euro-2024-champions |access-date=2024-07-15 |website=Saudi Professional League Association}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Laporte usually plays as a left-sided centre-back. Spanish football journalist [[Guillem Balagué]] described Laporte as a "centre-back who can play from the back and is strong", adding that "he is certainly a powerful defender".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/12037/11220803/man-city-likely-to-sign-aymeric-laporte-for-60m-says-guillem-balague |title=Man City likely to sign Aymeric Laporte for £60m, says Guillem Balagué |website=Sky Sports |first=Guillem |last=Balagué |date=24 January 2018 |access-date=22 February 2018}}</ref> He is also known for his passing ability.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/the-game-dissected-why-aymeric-laporte-is-the-key-man-in-manchester-citys-premier-league-title-charge-m835r9dzb |title=The Game Dissected: why Aymeric Laporte is the key to Manchester City's hopes |work=The Times |last1=Clarke |first1=Tom |date=15 April 2019 |access-date=14 July 2021}}</ref>

==Personal life==
He is the second son of Lionel and Marie-José Laporte, both from Agen. His father worked in a supermarket while his mother was a hairdresser.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.larazon.es/deportes/futbol/bailarina-cita-basquet-boda-cuento-castillo-flechazo-espanol-ameryc-laporte_20240709668cea02c53ff80001724a18.html | title=Una bailarina, una cita en el basket y una boda de cuento con castillo: El flechazo español de Aymeric Laporte | date=9 July 2024 }}</ref> His younger brother Léo Laporte is also a professional footballer.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kid brother of Man City defender Laporte turns pro at Alaves |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/kid-brother-of-man-city-defender-laporte-turns-pro-at-alaves-31512993 |website=OneFootball |date=24 October 2020 |access-date=10 February 2021}}</ref> His paternal grandfather Pierre was a rugby player, while his maternal grandfather Jacques played tennis at a local level.

He is married to professional dancer and former [[Bilbao Basket]] cheerleader Sara Botello. She was born in Bilbao with Galician roots. They were married in June 2023 and have two daughters, born in 2021 and 2024.

